<item>
            <title>[MJAVADOC-406] Regression: MJAVADOC-398 commit changed wrong line</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-406</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;functionality&quot;/change behavior of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-398&quot; title=&quot;Classes from build output directory can cause failure&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MJAVADOC-398&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MJAVADOC-398&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should definitely be configurable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In our project we have to manually put a lot of dependencies into &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;additionalDependencies&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; section to restore the previously working behaviour which is a huge pain and does not scale (as we will be forced to update the dependencies every time dependencies are added to projects).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please provide a javadoc configuration for turning on/off the &quot;functionality&quot; added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-398&quot; title=&quot;Classes from build output directory can cause failure&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MJAVADOC-398&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MJAVADOC-398&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12804474">MJAVADOC-406</key>
            <summary>Regression: MJAVADOC-398 commit changed wrong line</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="2" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/critical.svg">Critical</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
